<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-12-27T15:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-12-27T15:00:00-05:00" n="1019" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1019">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.12/127.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Brazilian Minister of Mexico</gloss>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-12-27T15:00:00-05:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">December 27, 1914, 3 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>378. Please tell Villa that this Government greatly appreciates his
                            friendly interest manifested in agreeing to the arrangement proposed by
                            General Scott in regard to cessation of firing along the international
                            border, of which we received notice last night through Confidential
                            Agent Llorente.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>